      </span>
   </div><h1>Singapore water polo team criticised for 'inappropriate' swimming trunks
<br/>
   </h1><h2 class="h2">A water polo team were given a dressing down on Thursday for wearing trunks with an &lsquo;inappropriate&rsquo; likeness of their state flag.
<br/>
   </h2><div class="art-fd fd-gr1-b clrd"><div class="sport rel-tags"><dl class="l-gr5 lh-cc"><dt class="cc fb">Related Tags:</dt><dd class=""><a href="/explore/locations/countries/singapore">Singapore</a></dd><dd class="bdr-cc bdr-l"><a href="/explore/locations/countries/china">China</a></dd></dl></div>
</div><div class="img-cnt figure">
      <img src="http://img.metro.co.uk/i/pix/2010/11/26/article-1290765054455-0C3B4164000005DC-762072_636x300.jpg" width="636" height="300" alt="Singapore men's water polo team players in their controversial trunks at the Asian Games (Pic: PA)"/>
      <span class="img-cap legend">Singapore men's water polo team players in their controversial trunks at the Asian Games (Pic: PA)</span>
   </div></div><div class="clrd"><div class="art-lft"><p>The Singapore men raised eyebrows at the Asian Games in China with the moon on groin design.</p><p>Their government said they should show &lsquo;dignity&rsquo; to the flag.</p><p>A statement from the country&rsquo;s Information Ministry declared: &lsquo;Unfortunately the team did not seek our advice on the use of the crescent moon and stars when they designed their swim trunks.</p><div class="img-cnt figure">
      <img src="http://img.metro.co.uk/i/pix/2010/11/26/article-1290766152066-0C3B2159000005DC-370180_466x373.jpg" width="466" height="373" alt="The Singapore government said the design was 'inappropriate' (AFP/Getty)"/>
      <span class="img-cap legend">The Singapore government said the design was 'inappropriate' (AFP/Getty)</span>
   </div><p>&lsquo;We would have told them that their design is inappropriate as we want elements of the flag to be treated with dignity.&rsquo;</p><p>The rules of the Asian Games stipulate a team's uniform cannot be changed in the middle of the tournament, so the Singapore government will have to allow the water polo players wear the controversial trunks for the rest of the competition. &nbsp;</p><p>The team has apologised for the placement of the flag and confirmed the trunks would not be used again after the Games.</p><p>&lsquo;We didn't have the slightest intention to do anything funny on our trunks to insult Singapore,&rsquo; team manager Samuel Wong told the Straits Times.</p><div class="sport m12 clrd clr-l p5t"><div class="clrd art-fd fd-gr1-b "><div class="flt-l facebookLike"><fb:like show_faces="true" ref="ITO=socialnet-facebook-like" layout="standard" href="http://www.metro.co.uk/sport/oddballs/848499-singapore-water-polo-team-criticised-for-inappropriate-swimming-trunks" width="370"></fb:like></div><div class="flt-r" style=""><a href="http://twitter.com/share" data-via="Metro_Sport" data-count="vertical" data-url="http://www.metro.co.uk//sport/oddballs/848499-singapore-water-polo-team-criticised-for-inappropriate-swimming-trunks?ITO=socialnet-twitter-button" class="twitter-share-button">Tweet</a></div></div>
</div><div class="fd-gr1-b clrd google-article"><div><script type="text/javascript"><!--[CDATA[
